main event: A single bright object, similar in appearance to a satellite, was observed visually in the air over the Pacific Ocean.
interesting points: The object was observed at coordinates 33-35N 164-10E on November 28, 1967 at 1559Z.
The object had a low position angle of 10 and was traveling on a course of 270 degrees true.
The weather conditions were reported as sea rough with clear skies and scattered clouds.
The report states that the information was not adequate for a proper evaluation, and the object was considered a possible aircraft sighting.
No physical evidence such as photographs was available.
sighted object: a single bright object, similar in appearance to a satellite
